item.title: Oil Tanker at Saudi Port Is Attacked
item.description: A boat loaded with explosives attacked an oil tanker docked at the Saudi port city of Jeddah in what the authorities there called an act of terrorism, the latest in a string of attacks on the kingdom’s oil infrastructure.

item.title: Singapore Aims to Vaccinate Population for Covid-19 by End-2021
item.description: Singapore’s prime minister said the country’s health authority has approved the Pfizer-BioNTech vaccine and Singapore expects to have the vaccine doses it needs from various suppliers by the third quarter of 2021.

item.title: A Student Was Murdered in Egypt. Italy Says It Has Solved the Mystery.
item.description: Italian prosecutors’ investigation into the torture and killing in Cairo of 28-year-old Giulio Regeni offers a rare look inside the workings of Egypt’s vast security state and shines a light on human-rights abuses in the country.

item.title: Fighting Wildfires Goes High Tech With Drones, Sensors and Satellites
item.description: As a new fire season begins in Australia, researchers are looking to rely more on technology—and less on people in towers with binoculars—to spot blazes quickly and better predict their path.

item.title: John le Carré Dies at 89
item.description: John le Carré, the spy-turned-novelist whose elegant and intricate narratives defined the Cold War espionage thriller and brought acclaim to a genre critics had once ignored, has died.

item.title: U.K., EU Leaders Extend Marathon Brexit Talks
item.description: The U.K. and European Union agreed “to go the extra mile” and keep negotiating over a new economic and security relationship, after previously saying they would decide by Sunday whether to call off the talks.
